This page contains information, syntax, and simple code examples, about the use of collections in Java.
Arrays Arrays.asList(array) Converts an array of objects into a list, great one-liner to use when you need to iterate over the array.
// Great way to create a collection within one line List&lt;String&gt; strings = Arrays.asList(&#34;one&#34;, &#34;two&#34;, &#34;three&#34;); Sets Copying/Cloning Sets Copy Constructor One way of copying a Set is to use the copy constructor of a Set implementation.
